data.meta_description: Argentinian tennis player David Nalbandian kicks an advertising board during the final of the Queen's club competition
data.text:
This article is more than 12 years old

Argentinian tennis player David Nalbandian kicks an advertising board during the final of the Queen's club competition in London, the traditional warm-up tournament for Wimbledon. Nalbandian was immediately disqualified after the incident, which left an official nursing a bloody leg. The trophy was handed to his opponent, Marin Cilic of Croatia
